INSTALLING AUTOMATICALLY
------------------------

The easiest way to install a perl module is to use the
CPAN or CPANPLUS methods.

This can be done in the following ways:

CPAN:

   % perl -MCPAN -e shell
   > install _MODULE_
   > quit

CPANPLUS:

   % cpanp
   > i _MODULE_
   > q

In both cases _MODULE_ is the name of the module. Please refer to the
documentation on CPAN or CPANPLUS for more information.


INSTALLING MANUALLY
-------------------

If Module::Build is installed, you can install it by running:

    perl Build.PL
    perl Build
    perl Build test
    perl Build install

Or using the older Makefile.PL method:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

